<subSubSection id="5DA66552FFCDFFC706F2F9B7FBCEF8E8" pageId="5" pageNumber="116" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="150336D9FFCDFFC706F2F9B7FBCEF8E8" blockId="5.[151,1437,1420,1951]" pageId="5" pageNumber="116">
<emphasis id="27C8EACBFFCDFFC706F2F9B7FED2F9D1" bold="true" box="[199,322,1564,1590]" pageId="5" pageNumber="116">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="D2BC4D5AFFCDFFC70450F9B7FD73F9D1" authority="Cho, 2022" authorityName="Cho" authorityYear="2022" box="[613,739,1564,1591]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Gonioctena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="116" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jolantae" status="new species and g.">
<emphasis id="27C8EACBFFCDFFC70450F9B7FDE9F9D1" box="[613,633,1564,1590]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="116">G</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="27C8EACBFFCDFFC704B2F9B7FD73F9D1" box="[647,739,1564,1590]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="116">jolantae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="3CFB57B0FFCDFFC704DFF9B7FC56F9D0" box="[746,966,1564,1591]" pageId="5" pageNumber="116" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="27C8EACBFFCDFFC704DFF9B7FCE3F9D1" bold="true" box="[746,883,1564,1590]" pageId="5" pageNumber="116">new species</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName id="D2BC4D5AFFCDFFC7059FF9B7FC56F9D0" box="[938,966,1564,1591]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Gonioctena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="116" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kamikawai">
<emphasis id="27C8EACBFFCDFFC7059FF9B7FC2EF9D1" box="[938,958,1564,1590]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="116">G</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicName>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
<emphasis id="27C8EACBFFCDFFC705F8F9B7FBD6F9D1" box="[973,1094,1564,1590]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="116">kamikawai</emphasis>
, in that the pronotum has nine black spots and the elytral punctures are arranged in irregular single or double rows. However, 
<taxonomicName id="D2BC4D5AFFCDFFC702E2F9EBFADAF9BD" authorityName="Cho" authorityYear="2022" box="[1239,1354,1600,1627]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Gonioctena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="116" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fujiana">
<emphasis id="27C8EACBFFCDFFC702E2F9EBFB7BF9BD" box="[1239,1259,1600,1626]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="116">G</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="27C8EACBFFCDFFC702CEF9EBFADAF9BD" box="[1275,1354,1600,1626]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="116">fujiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished by the following characters: irregular yellowish-brown marking on elytral humerus extending across half of elytral base (3/5 of base in 
<taxonomicName id="D2BC4D5AFFCDFFC70426F923FD01F945" authority="Cho, 2022" authorityName="Cho" authorityYear="2022" box="[531,657,1672,1699]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Gonioctena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="116" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jolantae" status="new species">
<emphasis id="27C8EACBFFCDFFC70426F923FDB7F945" box="[531,551,1672,1698]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="116">G</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="27C8EACBFFCDFFC70400F923FD01F945" box="[565,657,1672,1698]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="116">jolantae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="27C8EACBFFCDFFC704A2F923FCB0F945" bold="true" box="[663,800,1672,1698]" pageId="5" pageNumber="116">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="3CFB57B0FFCDFFC704A2F923FCB0F945" box="[663,800,1672,1698]" pageId="5" pageNumber="116" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, 1/3–3/5 of base in 
<taxonomicName id="D2BC4D5AFFCDFFC705C8F923FB07F945" box="[1021,1175,1672,1699]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Gonioctena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="116" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kamikawai">
<emphasis id="27C8EACBFFCDFFC705C8F923FB81F945" box="[1021,1041,1672,1698]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="116">G</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="27C8EACBFFCDFFC7022BF923FB07F945" box="[1054,1175,1672,1698]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="116">kamikawai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); median lobe parallelsided with apical process broader than shaft, lateral angles of process distinct (subparallel-sided with apical process narrower than median lobe, lateral angles of process rounded in 
<taxonomicName id="D2BC4D5AFFCDFFC70549F97BFC6CF90D" authority="Cho, 2022" authorityName="Cho" authorityYear="2022" box="[892,1020,1744,1771]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Gonioctena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="116" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jolantae" status="new species">
<emphasis id="27C8EACBFFCDFFC70549F97BFC00F90D" box="[892,912,1744,1770]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="116">G</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="27C8EACBFFCDFFC70595F97BFC6CF90D" box="[928,1020,1744,1770]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="116">jolantae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="27C8EACBFFCDFFC70230F97BFB01F90D" bold="true" box="[1029,1169,1744,1770]" pageId="5" pageNumber="116">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="3CFB57B0FFCDFFC70230F97BFB01F90D" box="[1029,1169,1744,1770]" pageId="5" pageNumber="116" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
; subparallel-sided with apical process narrower than the median lobe, lateral angles distinct in 
<taxonomicName id="D2BC4D5AFFCDFFC70587F95FFBDDF8E9" box="[946,1101,1780,1807]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Gonioctena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="116" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kamikawai">
<emphasis id="27C8EACBFFCDFFC70587F95FFC56F8E9" box="[946,966,1780,1806]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="116">G</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="27C8EACBFFCDFFC705E1F95FFBDDF8E9" box="[980,1101,1780,1806]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="116">kamikawai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
